Neptune is just too beautiful. Neptune's distinctive blue color comes from methane in its atmosphere, which absorbs red light and reflects blue light. While the planet's atmosphere is mostly hydrogen and helium, the presence of methane creates the visible blue hue. Additionally, Rayleigh scattering, which is the same process that makes Earth's sky blue, contributes to Neptune's blue appearance. Not just this, Neptune also has rains of diamonds.
